ZH: 我每天都会经过那个报亭。
EN: I pass by that newsstand every day.

ZH: 他在报亭买了一份最新的报纸。
EN: He bought the latest newspaper at the newsstand.

ZH: 这个报亭的店员很友好。
EN: The newsstand clerk is very friendly.

ZH: 你可以在那个报亭找到各种杂志。
EN: You can find all kinds of magazines at that newsstand.

ZH: 她在报亭买了一杯热咖啡。
EN: She bought a hot coffee at the newsstand.

ZH: 这个报亭的位置很好，生意应该会很好。
EN: The newsstand's location is great, business should be good.

ZH: 我刚才看到了一个漂亮的花束在报亭旁边的花店。
EN: I just saw a beautiful bouquet of flowers at the flower shop next to the newsstand.

ZH: 这个报亭卖的零食种类很多。
EN: The newsstand sells a variety of snacks.

ZH: 我从报亭买了一本畅销书。
EN: I bought a best-selling book from the newsstand.

ZH: 雨下得如此之大，报亭前都没有人。
EN: The rain was so heavy that there was no one in front of the newsstand.

ZH: 他在报亭等了一个小时，但还是没等到他的朋友。
EN: He waited at the newsstand for an hour, but still didn't see his friend.

ZH: 这家报亭的货架上摆满了各种杂志。
EN: The newsstand's shelves are stocked with all kinds of magazines.

ZH: 她每天早上都会在报亭买一杯咖啡。
EN: She buys a cup of coffee from the newsstand every morning.

ZH: 那个报亭在街上的角落里。
EN: The newsstand is on the corner of the street.

ZH: 我在报亭找到了我一直在找的那本小说。
EN: I found the novel I have been looking for at the newsstand.

ZH: 我们可以在报亭里休息一下。
EN: We can take a break in the newsstand.

ZH: 他们的报亭生意非常好。
EN: Their newsstand business is doing very well.

ZH: 我们应该在报亭见面。
EN: Let's meet at the newsstand.

ZH: 经过报亭的时候，他注意到有新版的报纸上架了。
EN: As he passed by the newsstand, he noticed that there were new newspapers on display.

ZH: 报亭里提供免费的地图。
EN: The newsstand offers free maps.
